{{Infobox news event | title = December 2012 Lesbos, Greece migrant boat disaster | image = | image_name = | image_size = | caption = | date = {{start date|2012|12|14}} | time = Early hours | place = Off [[Lesbos]], Greece | coordinates = | also known as = | cause = | participants = Illegal migrants from [[Iraq]] | outcome = Boat sank | reported injuries = | reported death(s) = 18 | reported missing = 9 | reported property damage = | burial = | inquiries = | inquest = | coroner = | suspects = | charges = | verdict = | convictions = | publication bans = | litigation = | awards = | url = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | notes = }}
The '''December 2012 Lesbos, Greece migrant boat disaster''' occurred in the early hours of December 14, 2012, off [[Greece|Greek]] island [[Lesbos]] in the northeastern [[Aegean Sea]] when a boat carrying illegal immigrants, which set sail from [[Turkey]], sank. At least 18 people died by the incident, eight were missing and one man was rescued by the Greek harbor police.<ref name="w">{{cite news |url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article112041148/Mindestens-18-Menschen-vor-Griechenland-ertrunken.html |newspaper=[[Die Welt]] |title=Mindestens 18 Menschen vor Griechenland ertrunken |date=2012-12-15 |language=German |accessdate=2012-12-15 }}</ref><ref name="h">{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/planet/22165027.asp |newspaper=[[Hürriyet]] |title=Ege’de göçmen dramı: 18 ölü |author=Kırbaki, Yorgo |date=2012-12-15 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2012-12-15 }}</ref><ref name="u">{{cite web |url=http://www.ubalert.com/s84 |publisher=Disaster Alert Network |title= 15 Killed as Boat with illegal Migrants Sinks Near Greek Island |accessdate=2012-12-15 }}</ref>
According to the report of local authorities, 18 dead bodies were found stranded at the coast of [[Loutropoli Thermis|Thermis]] west of the island. The survivor, a man of age 20, stated that a total of 28 people of [[Iraq]]i nationality, including children, were aboard a small boat, which departed from the Turkish coast shortly after midnight on Thursday. After about one hour of sailing, the boat capsized due to bad weather conditions about {{convert|2.2|nmi|km|abbr=on}} before the Greek coast. He added that they had paid US$2,000 per capita for the illegal immigration transport.<ref name="w"/><ref name="h"/>
